En África, internet es el celular
Lo cuentan en <a href="http://whiteafrican.com/?p=663">Again, Mobile Phones are Africa's PC</A>.

<blockquote>
The resounding story is this; Africans, and those creating things in
Africa, are doing it with the mobile phone. It's not that they are ignoring
the web, it's that they realize first hand that the mobile phone is the
platform of the masses. Any serious penetration of web-like structures,
information and connections will have to take place there.
</blockquote>

Yo, que ya lo había dicho en vidas anteriores (por ejemplo en <a href="http://fernand0.blogalia.com/historias/27429">Internet y los telefonillos</a>, veo que los africanos nos lo van a enseñar por la vía del ejemplo. 

Lo vi en <a href="http://www.globalvoicesonline.org/2007/07/01/africa-mobile-phones-are-africas-pc/">Africa: mobile phones are Africa's PC</a>.


